  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the outcomes of treating epidemic
      keratoconjunctivitis with 2% povidone-iodine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study design was a prospective interventional case series. Our institutional ethical
      committee approved the study protocol in April 2004. We performed this study between July
      2004 and December 2009. During this period, there were 2 episodes of EKC epidemic. The first
      episode was in 2006 and the second in 2009.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
